# Git Commit Message Conventions

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
```

## Types

| Type | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | New feature implementation |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code restructuring without behavior change |
| `docs` | Documentation changes |
| `style` | Formatting, missing semicolons, etc. |
| `test` | Adding or modifying tests |
| `chore` | Maintenance tasks, dependency updates |

## Scopes

Common scopes for this project:
- `button`, `dialog`, `input`, etc. - specific component
- `storybook` - Storybook configuration
- `eslint`, `prettier` - configuration
- `build` - build system
- `deps` - dependency updates

## Examples

```
feat(button): add icon position prop for icon buttons

- Added `iconName` and `iconPosition` props
- Icons can now be placed before or after label
- Backwards compatible change

Closes #123
```

```
fix(dialog): prevent modal from closing on backdrop click when static

- Added `static` prop for dialogs that shouldn't close on backdrop
- Updated Storybook stories to demonstrate new prop

Fixes #456
```

```
refactor(input): consolidate variant styles using CSS variables

- Reduced code duplication across variants
- Maintained exact same visual output
- All tests pass
```

```
test(button): add accessibility tests for all variants

- Added aria-disabled checks
- Verified tabindex behavior
- All Storybook tests pass
```

## Rules

1. Use imperative mood: "add" not "added", "fix" not "fixed"
2. Subject line max 72 characters
3. Body wrapped at 80 characters
4. Reference issues with `Closes #123` or `Fixes #456`
5. Breaking changes in footer: `BREAKING CHANGE: description`
6. Consider only staged changes for the commit message
